{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/asyncimage"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AsyncImage"},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"],"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:11OpenSwiftUI10AsyncImageV","symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncImage","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AsyncImage","kind":"identifier"}],"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/Image\/AsyncImage.swift#L77","fileName":"AsyncImage.swift"},"title":"AsyncImage","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"text":"A view that asynchronously loads and displays an image.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AsyncImage\/init(url:scale:)","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AsyncImage\/init(url:scale:content:placeholder:)","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AsyncImage\/init(url:scale:transaction:content:)"],"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AsyncImage\/body"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AsyncImage\/View-Implementations"],"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AsyncImage"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"Content"},{"kind":"text","text":"> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Content"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This view uses the shared"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/Foundation\/URLSession","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance to load an image from the specified URL, and then display it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, you can display an icon that’s stored on a server:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["AsyncImage(url: URL(string: \"https:\/\/example.com\/icon.png\"))","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Until the image loads, the view displays a standard placeholder that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fills the available space. After the load completes successfully, the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"updates to display the image. In the example above, the icon is smaller"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than the frame, and so appears smaller than the placeholder."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can specify a custom placeholder using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AsyncImage\/init(url:scale:content:placeholder:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". With this initializer, you can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"also use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"content","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameter to manipulate the loaded image.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, you can add a modifier to make the loaded image resizable:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["AsyncImage(url: URL(string: \"https:\/\/example.com\/icon.png\")) { image in","    image.resizable()","} placeholder: {","    ProgressView()","}",".frame(width: 50, height: 50)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For this example, OpenSwiftUI shows a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProgressView"},{"type":"text","text":" first, and then the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"image scaled to fit in the specified frame:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can’t apply image-specific modifiers, like","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Image\/resizable(capInsets:resizingMode:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", directly to an ","type":"text"},{"code":"AsyncImage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Instead, apply them to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Image","type":"reference"},{"text":" instance that your ","type":"text"},{"code":"content","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"closure gets when defining the view’s appearance.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"important","type":"aside","name":"Important"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To gain more control over the loading process, use the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AsyncImage\/init(url:scale:transaction:content:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" initializer, which takes a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"text":" closure that receives an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AsyncImagePhase","type":"reference"},{"text":" to indicate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the state of the loading operation. Return a view that’s appropriate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for the current phase:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["AsyncImage(url: URL(string: \"https:\/\/example.com\/icon.png\")) { phase in","    if let image = phase.image {","        image \/\/ Displays the loaded image.","    } else if phase.error != nil {","        Color.red \/\/ Indicates an error.","    } else {","        Color.blue \/\/ Acts as a placeholder.","    }","}"]}]}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/AsyncImagePhase":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The current phase of the asynchronous image loading operation.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AsyncImagePhase","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AsyncImagePhase"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"AsyncImagePhase"}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/asyncimagephase","type":"topic","title":"AsyncImagePhase","kind":"symbol"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Image":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Image"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/image","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Image"}],"title":"Image","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/document